radiographic_examinations.findings: Appendix is dilated and fluid-filled measuring up to 13 mm with adjacent free fluid. No discrete fluid collection or extra luminal air to suggest perforation. Lack of circumferential mural enhancement of the posterior lateral appendiceal wall likely reflective of gangrenous appendicitis. Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. Liver, pancreas, spleen, kidneys, bladder, and adrenal glands appear normal. No abnormal lymphadenopathy or vascular disease noted.
